By indication, the market segmentation highlights the key therapeutic areas where antispasmodics drugs are extensively utilized. Irritable bowel syndrome, characterized by abdominal pain and cramping, represents a significant segment for these drugs. Overactive bladder and gastroesophageal reflux disease are also prominent indications where antispasmodics play a crucial role in managing symptoms and improving patients' quality of life. The segmentation based on indication provides a comprehensive view of the market dynamics, shedding light on the specific needs of patients across different healthcare settings.

